SIMPLE: roan
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Roan
<hw>Roan</hw> <pr>(r⟦omac⟧n)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>rouan</ets>; cf. Sp. <ets>roano</ets>, <ets>ruano</ets>, It.
<ets>rovano</ets>, <ets>roano</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having a
bay, chestnut, brown, or black color, with gray or white thickly
interspersed; -- said of a horse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Give my <qex>roan</qex> a drench.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Made of the leather called roan; <as>as,
<ex>roan</ex> binding</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Roan antelope</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a very
large South African antelope (<spn>Hippotragus equinus</spn>). It has
long sharp horns and a stiff bright brown mane. Called also
<altname>mahnya</altname>, <altname>equine antelope</altname>, and
<altname>bastard gemsbok</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Roan</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Roan
<hw>Roan</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The color of a roan horse;
a roan color.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A roan horse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A kind of leather used for slippers, bookbinding,
etc., made from sheepskin, tanned with sumac and colored to imitate
ungrained morocco.</def> <rj><au>DeColange.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Roan tree</b></col>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <cd>See <er>Rowan
tree</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Roar</ent>⟦br⟧
